### Phase 6: Backend Credential CRUD (4 files) (CHECKPOINT)

**Goal:** Add backend credential storage and resolution for the new provider.

**CHECKPOINT -- Before writing backend code, present to the user:**

1. The credential model struct fields (name, Go type, BSON tag, JSON tag) derived from the proto config.
2. Whether an auth method discriminator field is needed (only for multi-method providers).
3. The required-field validation that will be enforced in the service layer.

**Ask for confirmation.** If the user corrects anything, update before proceeding.

**Step 6.1 -- MODIFY `app/backend/pkg/models/credential.go`**

Add the credential struct at the end of the file:

```go
// <ProviderDisplayName>Credential represents <ProviderDisplayName> credentials.
type <ProviderPascal>Credential struct {
    ID        primitive.ObjectID `bson:"_id,omitempty" json:"id"`
    Name      string             `bson:"name" json:"name"`
    // ... provider-specific fields with bson/json tags ...
    CreatedAt time.Time          `bson:"created_at" json:"created_at"`
    UpdatedAt time.Time          `bson:"updated_at" json:"updated_at"`
}
```

For multi-method providers, add an `AuthMethod string` field (see `OpenStackCredential`).

**Pattern reference:** `ScalewayCredential` struct in `app/backend/pkg/models/credential.go`

**Step 6.2 -- MODIFY `app/backend/internal/database/credential_repo.go`**

Add 3 methods and 1 switch case:

1. `Create<ProviderPascal>()` -- creates a new credential document with provider-specific fields
2. `Update<ProviderPascal>()` -- updates an existing credential document
3. `convertTo<ProviderPascal>Credential()` -- converts a BSON document to the credential model
4. In `FindFirstByProvider()` switch, add: `case "<provider_package>": return convertTo<ProviderPascal>Credential(result)`

**Pattern reference:** `CreateScaleway`, `UpdateScaleway`, `convertToScalewayCredential` in `credential_repo.go`

**Step 6.3 -- MODIFY `app/backend/internal/service/credential_service.go`**

Add switch cases and helper functions:

1. **Create switch** (in `Create` method): add `case credentialv1.Credential_<PROVIDER_UPPER>: return s.create<ProviderPascal>Credential(ctx, req.Msg.Name, req.Msg.ProviderConfig, now)`
2. **Update switch** (in `Update` method): add `case credentialv1.Credential_<PROVIDER_UPPER>: return s.update<ProviderPascal>Credential(ctx, req.Msg.Id, req.Msg.Name, req.Msg.ProviderConfig)`
3. **List switch** (both the provider-to-string and string-to-provider mappings)
4. **Get switch** (converts BSON to proto credential)
5. **Helper functions:**
   - `create<ProviderPascal>Credential()` -- validates required fields, converts proto to model, calls repo
   - `update<ProviderPascal>Credential()` -- validates required fields, converts proto to model, calls repo
   - `<provider_package>ProtoToModel()` -- converts proto config to database model
   - `<provider_package>ModelToProtoConfig()` -- converts database model back to proto config
   - `convertBsonTo<ProviderPascal>Credential()` -- converts raw BSON to credential model

Add the provider proto import: `<provider_alias> "github.com/plantonhq/openmcf/apis/org/openmcf/provider/<provider_package>"`

**Pattern reference:** Search for `scaleway` (case-insensitive) in `credential_service.go` to see all touch points.

**Step 6.4 -- MODIFY `app/backend/internal/service/credential_resolver.go`**

Add a case in the `ResolveProviderConfig` switch:

```go
case cloudresourcekind.CloudResourceProvider_<provider_id>:
    cred := credInterface.(*models.<ProviderPascal>Credential)
    return &credentialv1.CredentialProviderConfig{
        Data: &credentialv1.CredentialProviderConfig_<ProviderPascal>{
            <ProviderPascal>: &<provider_alias>.<ProtoConfigName>{
                // Map all model fields to proto fields
            },
        },
    }, nil
```

For multi-method providers, reconstruct the oneof from the stored auth method discriminator (see the OpenStack case).

Add the provider proto import.

**Pattern reference:** The Scaleway case in `credential_resolver.go`

