### Phase 8: Catalog Documentation (2-3 files) (CHECKPOINT)

**Goal:** Add the provider to the public documentation catalog.

**CHECKPOINT -- Ask the user:**

1. "Do you have an SVG icon for <ProviderDisplayName>? If so, please provide the file path. Otherwise, I will reference `default.svg` in the catalog."
2. "Any specific description or resource list you want on the provider catalog page, or should I create a minimal placeholder indicating resources are coming soon?"

**Step 8.1 -- CREATE `site/public/docs/catalog/<provider_package>/index.md`**

```markdown
---
title: "<PROVIDER_UPPER>"
description: "Deploy <PROVIDER_UPPER> resources using OpenMCF"
icon: "cloud"
order: <next_order_number>
---

# <PROVIDER_UPPER>

<ProviderDisplayName> provider registered. Deployment components coming soon.

For more information about <ProviderDisplayName>, see the [<ProviderDisplayName> Documentation](<provider_docs_url>).
```

If the user provides a list of planned resources, include them as a bullet list instead of the placeholder text.

**Step 8.2 -- CREATE or PLACE `site/public/images/providers/<provider_package>.svg`**

If the user provides an SVG, place it here. Otherwise, note that `default.svg` will be used in the catalog index.

**Step 8.3 -- MODIFY `site/public/docs/catalog/index.md`**

